ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: On average, how often do you have scheduled individual supervision (One-on-one meeting between you and supervisor to address formal supervision including feedback, teaching/coaching, suggestions, discussing worker feelings or specific cases, administrative matters, information on policies and procedures, or coordinating work)?
Notes: 1= Never; 2= Quarterly or less often; 3= Once every month or two; 4= Monthly; 5= 2-3 times a month; 6= Weekly; 7= More than once a week; 999= NK/Missing

ElementDescription: On average, how long does the scheduled individual supervision session last (in minutes)?
Notes: Number of minutes; 999= NK/Missing

ElementDescription: On average, how often do you have scheduled group supervision (Group meeting between team members and supervisor or between team members for peer-based supervision)?
Notes: 1= Never; 2= Quarterly or less often; 3= Once every month or two; 4= Monthly; 5= 2-3 times a month; 6= Weekly; 7= More than once a week; 999= NK/Missing

ElementDescription: On average, how long does the scheduled group supervision session last (in minutes)?
Notes: Number of minutes; 999= NK/Missing

ElementDescription: Thinking about this informal supervision (interactions with a supervisor outside of formal/scheduled supervision times), on average, how often do you have informal individual supervision?
Notes: 1= Never; 2= Quarterly or less often; 3= Once every month or two; 4= Monthly; 5= 2-3 times a month; 6= Weekly; 7= More than once a week; 999= NK/Missing
